Defendant Author Jack Johnson in court with attorney Eric Daniel Lowenberg.  Sarra Kiaie appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
cab
Parties are in court for re-sentencing.
Court vacated the previous sentence and re-sentenced the defendant as follows:
  Statements made as to sentencing.  Additional statement/s by:  Tiffany J.
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 27 MONTHS, with credit for -0- DAYS time served; consecutive to current sentence, the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 15 MONTHS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 12 MONTHS. 
The Court STAYED this sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 30 MONTHS, concurrent,  with the following conditions:
*   Successfully complete Parenting Classes.
*   No violent contact with the victim or anyone else. 
*   Pay supervision fees;
*   Provide a DNA sample
*  The court ordered defendant to pay the mandatory costs and supervision fees during probation; failure to pay will result in a civil judgment. The court found that the defendant is indigent and imposed the DNA sample but waived the surcharge for it.
.
*** If the defendant has already paid the supervision fees and submitted a DNA sample, the court will waive that requirement.
.
The defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Substance Abuse Program.
The Court advised the defendant that as a convicted felon he/she may not vote until his/her civil rights are restored and he/she may never possess a firearm..
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.
Credit form filed.
. 
Supervision may be transferred to Arizona.
.
Postconviction notice filed.
